{"tid":307871,"cid":33,"subCid":0,"title":"[突發] 梁天琦訪問英國國會  與國會議員 Nigel Evans 會面","createTime":"2017-07-03T16:27:19.000Z","updateTime":"2017-07-03T16:58:58.000Z","uid":79563,"like":9,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":0,"replies":[{"pid":"1598c77997717ea8e7cad53a2dfc1de2998ab6fc","tid":307871,"uid":79563,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-07-03T16:27:19.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/HKCPForum/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FHKCPForum%2F&d=h1MB3VLklj48%2BH4sCaN85XIou9iuErJt32EjuWI86Zw%3D&h=8b933aad\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/HKCPForum/</a><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://scontent.fhkg1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/19598915_1769252229759603_6621607392110710792_n.jpg?oh=0cce3d7d7ccf5fd5f70b82aa24909bb3&amp;oe=5A08EB4E\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fscontent.fhkg1-1.fna.fbcdn.net%2Fv%2Ft1.0-9%2F19598915_1769252229759603_6621607392110710792_n.jpg%3Foh%3D0cce3d7d7ccf5fd5f70b82aa24909bb3%26oe%3D5A08EB4E&h=1cda48c1&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://scontent.fhkg1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/19756459_1769252226426270_4581795497777347611_n.jpg?oh=2acbe12c2ffba2b2dafab07fe397949a&amp;oe=59CBD673\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fscontent.fhkg1-1.fna.fbcdn.net%2Fv%2Ft1.0-9%2F19756459_1769252226426270_4581795497777347611_n.jpg%3Foh%3D2acbe12c2ffba2b2dafab07fe397949a%26oe%3D59CBD673&h=395f493b&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://scontent.fhkg1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/19642288_1769252233092936_6691365425351222054_n.jpg?oh=4d59c1cbed008ba4781bef165b0de5a8&amp;oe=59CE1153\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fscontent.fhkg1-1.fna.fbcdn.net%2Fv%2Ft1.0-9%2F19642288_1769252233092936_6691365425351222054_n.jpg%3Foh%3D4d59c1cbed008ba4781bef165b0de5a8%26oe%3D59CE1153&h=d9cb5234&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nWelcome to join today's Parliamentary event! Edward Leung 梁天琦 will present &quot; The future of HK&rsquo;s Localism Movement&rdquo; at Henry Jackson Society and &quot;Hong Kong's Democratic Deficit&quot; at UK Parliament Committee Room on July 3. Another speaker from Hong Kong is Anson Chan. There are two events. <br />\n1. Parliamentary event is open to public. Interested parties should message us for further details. You must arrive before 5:30pm to go through Parliament security. It could take 20 mins. <br />\n2. For Henry Jackson Society event, the registration was closed. The selected participants were informed by emails. Thank you!<br />\n<br />\nEvents details below: <br />\n<br />\nThe 20th Anniversary of Hong Kong&rsquo;s Handover<br />\n<br />\n1. <strong><span style=\"color: orange;\">Parliamentary Event</span></strong>, Committee Room 20, Palace of Westminster/ UK Parliament July 3 Monday at 6pm <br />\n<br />\nSession Three: Future Expectations for Hong Kong<br />\n<br />\nChair: <strong><span style=\"color: orange;\">Nigel Evans MP</span></strong><br />\nSpeaker 1: Sir Malcolm Rifkind, KCMG, QC, &ldquo;British thinking on Hong Kong&rdquo; <br />\nSpeaker 2: Edward Leung, Hong Kong Indigenous, &ldquo;Hong Kong&rsquo;s Democratic Deficit&rdquo; <br />\nSpeaker 3: Dr. Malte Kaeding, Univ. of Surrey, &ldquo;Dynamics between HK and Beijing&rdquo; <br />\nSpeaker 4: Anson Chan, GCMG, CBE, JP, &ldquo;The future of Hong Kong&rsquo;s democracy&rdquo; <br />\nDiscussion, Q&amp;A<br />\n<br />\n2. Closed-door Event at Henry Jackson Society July 3 at 2pm <br />\nSession One: 1997 Historical Legacies of the Handover<br />\nChair: John Hemmings, Henry Jackson Society<br />\nSpeaker 1: Amb. Hugh Davies CMG, &ldquo;British Perspectives and Negotiations from the JLG&rdquo; Prof. <br />\nSpeaker 2: Carol Jones, Univ. of Birmingham, &ldquo;The Rule of Law under pressure&rdquo; <br />\nSpeaker 3: Anson Chan, GCMG, CBE, JP, &ldquo;Hong Kong politics during the Handover&rdquo; <br />\nDiscussion, Q&amp;A<br />\nSession Two: 2017 International and Economic Dimensions<br />\nChair: James Miles, The Economist<br />\nSpeaker 1: Prof. Steve Tsang, SOAS, &ldquo;Beijing and Hong Kong Relations&rdquo;<br />\nSpeaker 2: Dr. Malte Kaeding, Univ. of Surrey, &ldquo;The Taiwan-HK-China Nexus&rdquo;<br />\nSpeaker 3: John Calverley, Chief Economist, Calverley Economic Advs, Ltd. &ldquo;HK-China Economy&rdquo; <br />\nSpeaker 4: Edward Leung, Hong Kong Indigenous, &ldquo;The future of HK&rsquo;s Localism Movement&rdquo; <br />\nDiscussion, Q&amp;A"},{"pid":"351dd98aea2982613174a33539fb957e7a751c78","tid":307871,"uid":319,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-07-03T16:27:49.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a02d9227251615e5026fc99d4a61b0c35c3f5087","tid":307871,"uid":13781,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-07-03T16:33:29.000Z","msg":"外交<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"c6102c62dede26f2bf9611794c6d3d5d888025a0","tid":307871,"uid":30807,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-07-03T16:34:26.000Z","msg":"成日恰鳩我英文差<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a823cce43e765405252b70c7f9ea578e3ceb106a","tid":307871,"uid":19501,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-07-03T16:35:39.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"e7ac0adf3e4ab937f8b107be3432dab81549fd0a","tid":307871,"uid":7369,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"